    Instantiate the object on a value init file. This will configure a working directory that stages all input and output files.

    In [3]:
    Copied! 
    FILE = 'data/basic4/cu_hxr.in'

G = Genesis4(FILE, verbose = True)
    FILE = 'data/basic4/cu_hxr.in' G = Genesis4(FILE, verbose = True)
    Configured to run in: /var/folders/2f/l5_mybzs30j4qqvyj98w1_nw0000gn/T/tmplpt6ynu8

    Fields¶

    Field files can be very large and are not loaded by default. Instead, the files found are collected as a list:

    In [11]:
    Copied! 
    G.output['field_files']
    G.output['field_files']
    Out[11]:
    ['/var/folders/2f/l5_mybzs30j4qqvyj98w1_nw0000gn/T/tmplpt6ynu8/end.fld.h5']

    This will load all files in the list

    In [12]:
    Copied! 
    G.load_field_files()
    G.load_field_files()
    Loaded field data: end
    In [13]:
    Copied! 
    G.output['field'].keys()
    G.output['field'].keys()
    Out[13]:
    dict_keys(['end'])

    Plotting¶

    Convenient plotting of the data in .output is provided by .plot. The default is to plot the power. Note that these statistics are averaged over all slices.

    In [26]:
    Copied! 
    G.plot()
    G.plot()

    Left and right axes can be set this way:

    In [27]:
    Copied! 
    G.plot('power', y2 = ['beam_xsize', 'beam_ysize'])
    G.plot('power', y2 = ['beam_xsize', 'beam_ysize'])
    In [28]:
    Copied! 
    G.plot(['field_xsize', 'field_ysize'])
    G.plot(['field_xsize', 'field_ysize'])
    In [29]:
    Copied! 
    plt.imshow(G.output['Field/power'], aspect='auto')
    plt.imshow(G.output['Field/power'], aspect='auto')
